						               													<description>Welcome to Little Drawington, a small sleepy village on a hill in the British countryside that prides itself on their beautiful gardens and friendly community. As the days get shorter and the leaves start to change, excitement rises in the village as they get to work on their autumn gardens for the Pumpkin Growing Contest. This year, the competition is extra fierce, there are strange rumours going around of unusual behaviour. It is the night before the grand jury comes by and you are not leaving anything to chance, calling upon dark forces from beyond to grow your pumpkin the biggest and even sabotaging your neighbours gardens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Little Drawington: Halloween is a draw and draw game, where players draw cards with shapes they then get to draw on their own garden boards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of 3 repeating phases and a final evaluation round The phases are: The Ghastly Growing Phase, the Creepy Carving Phase, and the Demonic Decoration Phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the deck of root cards has run out, the sun rises and players  add up their points. The player with the most points win. The garden boards look like little clipboards from the town council, so as players are creating their gardens they are also filling in what the garden looks like on a scoring form for the end of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
